On my last day in Scotland I wanted to visit a very special place. A place that I have seen for the first time back in April 2016. I never got it out of my mind so even with extreme weather and storms (gusts up to 160kmh) I decided to leave my warm and safe shelter and go see this place instead. Once I got there I stepped out of the car and heavy rain and winds immediately hit my face and took my breath away. I knew I couldn’t be out here for a long time and also taking proper pictures would be hardly possible but I still wanted to give it a try. After walking along the cliffs I got soaked within a few minutes and so got my camera. Nevertheless I managed to get a few shots of this breathtaking landscape. Since it was slowly getting dark I knew I had to make it back to the car but somehow underestimated the force of the wind. I was the last person out there and in the distance I could see one last tourist bus waiting in the parking lot. It took me twice as long to get back to the car but in the end I made it. I realized I wasn’t able to take the pictures that I had in my mind but in the end it was an experience that I never will forget. #hiddenscotland #collectmomentsnotthings #memoriesforalifetime

After I have visited this place for the first time in 2016, it was clear to me that I would have to go back someday! About a week ago it was time again. When I drove towards The Storr my heart started to beat faster. This time however the weather was so extreme that I almost didn't make it to the top. I was in many wild places but the weather that day was something else. My plan was to do a long hike around the area but after arriving at the top of the Old Man I had to return ... Soaked to the skin but happy I had to seek shelter from the heavy rain and storm. What a day! 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿 #scotland #isleofskye #highlands #oldmanofstorr

I am currently exploring the Scottish Highlands and the Ilse of Skye later this week. Don’t get me wrong! I am really digging the Scottish weather but today it is supposed to get really bad as remnants of hurricane Florence will hit the country. It’s going to be very stormy and rainy. Maybe whisky tasting it will be for today. Oh and here is an old photo of a little white deer standing in the woods. Have a great day!

Chilling by the Lake. Anzeige | One question I am getting asked quite a lot! "What is your favorite lens to shoot with Patrick?" Well to be honest this question is a tough one because there is not just one I like! However as a landscape photographer the Nikkor 14-24mm 1:2,8G ED is one of my all time favorite lenses. For me it is the perfect ultra wide-angle lens and with an aperture of 2,8 it even performs outstanding in low-light situations. Nevertheless I never would go without my Nikkor 70-200mm f2,8E FL ED VR - for me it is a must when it comes to animal portraits and landscape close-ups. What’s your favorite lens? 📷 #NikonDeutschland #NikonFamily

Neist Point Lighthouse, can be found on the most westerly tip of Skye and was first lit on 1 November 1909. From the path you will see stunning views of the high cliffs and the lighthouse itself, at sunset the view is made even more spectacular making this a top destination for landscape photographers. Can you spot the guardian of the lighthouse? #lighthouse #neistpoint #scotland

Anzeige* | Last week I got my hands on a brandnew Honor 10 smartphone and took it for a spin in my beautiful hometown Nuremberg. I was using the Pro Mode for taking this picture of the Heilig-Geist-Spital (Hospice of the Holy Spirit) but in case you just have started with photography and don´t know how to set up ISO, shutter speed etc. properly the phone has an excellent AI mode which is the perfect assistant when taking the first steps. The AI feature of the camera allows for great scenery recognition and makes it hardly impossible to mess up a shot! @honorglobal #HonorPlay #Honor10 #AIS

*Anzeige| Foggy days are just one of many reason why I love taking photos during the cold season. Other benefits are better, softer light, a higher chance of creating atmospheric shots and less competition on location. What’s your favorite season for photography? On a side note: this photo was being composed of 10 single images. The morning I took this photo I didn´t have my 14-24mm lens with me, which would have been necessary to fit the whole castle in just one frame. Instead, I was using my 24-70mm, took 10 single images and merged them together in the post-processing process. Sometimes I find this technique very helpful - have you ever tried it out? #NikonDeutschland #NikonFamily @nikondeutschland
